                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid red)</seg>
                        Scribe: Gabra Māryām. Gabra Māryām
                        is mentioned as the scribe in the supplication formula (<locus target="#35vb">35vb</locus>).<date>19th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓለ/ለዓ፡ ዓለ፡ አሜ፡/ ለዓለመ፡ ዓ፡ አሜ፡/ ለዓለመ፡ አ/ዓ፡ አ፡</abbr> for
                                 <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ </expan> (<locus target="#30va">30va</locus>, 43ra, 48vb, 50va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰ/ሰላ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#58ra">58ra</locus>, 60ra, 61va)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of
                           Texts I and III, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each
                           section of Texts I and III; incipit of Text II; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; the words salām (e.g.,
                           fols. 58ra, 59rb, 60ra), ʾaʾakkʷǝto (e.g., fol. 64ra), sǝb(ḥat) (e.g.,
                           fol. 64rb).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#3va">3va</locus>, 14vb, 30va: simple coloured (red and
                        black) ornamental bands; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r">f. 1r</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from the Book of the Covenant of Mercy.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The prayer is written in the main hand. Cp. <locus target="#20ra">20ra-</locus>
                           <note>b. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Erasures: <locus target="#6va">6va</locus>, 8ra, 12ra,
                           33vb.
 - Omitted letters and words written interlineally by a recent
                           hand, in pen: fols, 17ra, 20vb, 22va, 41va, 52vb, 54va.
 - Crude
                           drawing of the Eucharistic bread, the legend: mahtäm, in <locus target="#65v">65v</locus>.
 - Minor notes: <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 18r, 22r, 56v, 65v, 66v.
 - Writing exercises: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1v, 2r, 2v, 3r, 3v, 8v, 40r, 58r, 58v, 59r,
                           62v, 63r, 64r.
 - Doodles: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 2r, 2v,
                           16v, 17v, 35v, 36r, 64v, 65r, 66r.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Monthly readings are indicated with the names of the
                              months written in the upper margins: zä-Miyāzyā (<locus target="#13r">fol. 13r</locus>), zä-Gǝnbot (14v), zä-Näḥase (<locus target="#25v">fol. 25v</locus>), zä-Ṭǝqǝmt (<locus target="#34r">fol. 34r</locus>) zä-Ḫǝdar (<locus target="#37v">fol.
                              37v</locus>), zä-Ṭǝrr (<locus target="#47r">fol.
                           47r</locus>).</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
